1
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:44,780
My daughter looks so beautiful today.

2
00:00:46,190 --> 00:00:47,380
Thank you.

3
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:51,180
But... where are you taking me, Uncle?

4
00:00:51,330 --> 00:00:52,620
Call me "Dad," dear.

5
00:00:54,310 --> 00:00:56,810
If I told you, it wouldn't be a surprise.

6
00:00:58,840 --> 00:01:01,370
But, um... I mean...

7
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:03,640
Come on, just trust me.

8
00:01:03,990 --> 00:01:05,530
I guarantee you’re going to love it.

9
00:01:06,970 --> 00:01:07,470
Okay.

10
00:01:08,650 --> 00:01:09,990
Let’s go, or we’ll be late.

11
00:01:18,430 --> 00:01:19,910
The sales for this year are excellent.

12
00:01:19,940 --> 00:01:21,410
I really want to commend you all.

13
00:01:21,430 --> 00:01:22,390
Everyone did a great job.

14
00:01:22,410 --> 00:01:23,280
Everyone, excuse me.

15
00:01:24,690 --> 00:01:26,690
I have an announcement to make.

16
00:01:29,690 --> 00:01:33,560
Um... Uncle, why did you bring me here?

17
00:01:35,790 --> 00:01:37,650
I told you to call me Dad, Hm

18
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:43,110
This is Ranya, another daughter of mine.

19
00:01:46,230 --> 00:01:47,230
They don't look alike at all.

20
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:48,830
What is going on?

21
00:01:51,450 --> 00:01:55,390
From now on, she will be learning the ropes here as an heir.

22
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:59,890
She will be my successor

23
00:02:00,250 --> 00:02:01,300
alongside Pimchat.

24
00:02:03,740 --> 00:02:07,450
Please treat them both with equal respect.

25
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:28,080
Ran, how could you do this to me?

26
00:02:29,670 --> 00:02:31,370
You knew everything,

27
00:02:31,870 --> 00:02:33,870
you knew how much I love this company.

28
00:02:34,850 --> 00:02:36,180
And you still...

29
00:02:37,510 --> 00:02:43,960
Have you never trusted me at all this whole time?

30
00:03:09,930 --> 00:03:11,700
It’s impossible between us.

31
00:03:13,090 --> 00:03:14,390
You know that, P’Chat.

32
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,330
We are siblings.

33
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:27,680
From now on, I’m going to move on.

34
00:03:31,390 --> 00:03:36,070
And I hope you won’t cross the line again.

35
00:03:40,590 --> 00:03:41,160
Ran...

36
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:41,690
Excuse me.

37
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:47,280
Ran.

38
00:04:44,650 --> 00:04:46,910
What did you just say?

39
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:51,200
Uh... I mean, outsiders really aren't allowed to see these documents.

40
00:04:52,450 --> 00:04:56,230
You do know who I am, don't you?

41
00:04:57,980 --> 00:05:01,850
I do, but... I really can't let you see them.

42
00:05:02,410 --> 00:05:04,990
Otherwise, K’Chat will definitely scold me.

43
00:05:05,650 --> 00:05:11,090
In that case, I might have to tell K’ Wichai that the staff here...

44
00:05:12,230 --> 00:05:16,150
What are you threatening my employees for, K’Jintana?

45
00:05:21,290 --> 00:05:25,330
Oh, I just wanted to know how Ranya’s first day of work was going.

46
00:05:25,970 --> 00:05:28,470
And I’m also fulfilling my duty...

47
00:05:29,010 --> 00:05:33,350
My husband asked me to check if there’s anything suspicious going on at the company.

48
00:05:34,850 --> 00:05:38,070
So, I took the opportunity to bring lunch boxes for everyone.

49
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:39,630
There’s one for you too, Pimchat.

50
00:05:41,210 --> 00:05:41,990
No, thank you.

51
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:45,990
Well, at least give it a try.

52
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:48,260
I put my heart and soul into cooking this.

53
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:50,260
No, thank you.

54
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:53,820
What a shame.

55
00:05:54,610 --> 00:05:59,480
I even asked K’Wichai what your favorite dishes are.

56
00:05:59,910 --> 00:06:02,410
He told me quite a lot, you know.

57
00:06:08,470 --> 00:06:09,920
If I eat it, will that be enough?

58
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:13,640
Yes.

59
00:06:14,580 --> 00:06:19,380
I’m so glad the two of us are finally getting closer.

60
00:06:33,230 --> 00:06:35,490
I can't believe how dismissive people are here.

61
00:06:35,870 --> 00:06:37,070
I brought them coffee,

62
00:06:37,410 --> 00:06:39,410
and they’re not even said 'thank you'

63
00:06:41,230 --> 00:06:44,100
Seriously. If it weren't broad daylight,

64
00:06:44,130 --> 00:06:46,860
I’d think I was a ghost or something, completely invisible.

65
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,090
Anyway, I'm Nicha.

66
00:06:50,490 --> 00:06:51,450
I'm Ran.

67
00:06:52,990 --> 00:06:55,350
But yeah, you're right.

68
00:06:55,850 --> 00:06:58,700
I wonder what interns at other companies

69
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:01,350
are going through.

70
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:02,790
I’m actually curious.

71
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:06,720
Hey... if they had to deal with what we’re dealing with,

72
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:09,450
I bet they’d have all reported it to the Labor Department by now.

73
00:07:10,660 --> 00:07:13,010
Should we try doing that then?

74
00:07:13,860 --> 00:07:16,250
Are you crazy? This is your company!

75
00:07:16,730 --> 00:07:18,060
Just try a little bit. I think it will not be that bad.

76
00:07:18,090 --> 00:07:18,820
Absolutely not!

77
00:07:19,690 --> 00:07:21,090
I don't think it would do any damage.

78
00:07:21,130 --> 00:07:22,170
It’s absolutely damaging.

79
00:07:22,370 --> 00:07:24,590
just a little test. What’s the problem?

80
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:25,460
No way.

81
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:28,560
Are you still standing here smiling?

82
00:07:29,890 --> 00:07:31,890
Do you know you hurt Pimchat?

83
00:07:32,610 --> 00:07:33,120
Excuse me?

84
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:35,630
Don’t play innocent with me.

85
00:07:35,660 --> 00:07:36,940
You betrayed my friend.

86
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:38,290
What are you talking about?

87
00:07:38,610 --> 00:07:39,750
Who even are you?

88
00:07:39,770 --> 00:07:41,410
Why are you just showing up and attacking people like this?

89
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:42,590
Are you crazy?

90
00:08:02,460 --> 00:08:03,850
Watch your tone.

91
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,070
Do you know how much older I am than you?

92
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:10,190
I’m respectful to adults who deserve it.

93
00:08:10,550 --> 00:08:14,040
But for people who have no logic deserve to be told off.

94
00:08:18,970 --> 00:08:23,530
Oh, I see. No wonder you're friends.

95
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:27,310
Neither of you even realizes the wrongs you've done to other people.

96
00:08:27,540 --> 00:08:29,090
Don't group us together like that.

97
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:31,480
I’m a good person and so is my friend too.

98
00:08:33,090 --> 00:08:35,890
You don't even know what your friend has done,

99
00:08:36,380 --> 00:08:37,380
Yet here you are defending her.

100
00:08:37,410 --> 00:08:38,470
And what are you going to do about it?

101
00:08:38,490 --> 00:08:40,740
Hey... Do you even know who I am?

102
00:08:40,860 --> 00:08:41,770
Do you know?

103
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:44,110
Why would I need to know who you are?

104
00:08:44,830 --> 00:08:46,000
You’re so rude.

105
00:08:46,270 --> 00:08:47,550
Well, you’re not exactly respectable.

106
00:08:48,070 --> 00:08:49,910
An adult coming to told off a child like this?

107
00:08:50,430 --> 00:08:51,650
Why should I respect you?

108
00:09:35,070 --> 00:09:36,070
She’s so pity.

109
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:37,680
Even though she’s the President's daughter...

110
00:09:39,220 --> 00:09:41,310
That department is working her to the bone.

111
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:44,190
fine... it’s all part of the learning process.

112
00:09:44,230 --> 00:09:46,190
The more she does, the faster she’ll get the hang of things.

113
00:09:46,230 --> 00:09:47,090
You want to try it then?

114
00:10:08,910 --> 00:10:09,460
Ran!

115
00:10:10,650 --> 00:10:11,210
Ran!

116
00:10:12,540 --> 00:10:13,240
Ran,

117
00:10:13,410 --> 00:10:14,090
Inhaler!

118
00:10:14,450 --> 00:10:15,500
Someone get me some inhalers!

119
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:16,790
Does anyone have it?

120
00:10:17,370 --> 00:10:18,230
Ran!

121
00:10:19,230 --> 00:10:20,070
Ran!

122
00:10:20,390 --> 00:10:21,110
Ran!

123
00:10:21,770 --> 00:10:22,430
Ran!

124
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:23,510
Ran!

125
00:10:25,210 --> 00:10:26,560
Can you see me? Ran!

126
00:10:27,530 --> 00:10:28,130
Ran!

127
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:29,340
P’Chat...

128
00:10:31,970 --> 00:10:32,610
Ran!

129
00:10:38,370 --> 00:10:40,460
Who the hell has been overworking Ranya like this?

